from CrossProcessFrameConnector::OnVisibilityChanged().



This will be used in a subsequent CL to track visibility of frames

entry.title: Fix ChromeNetworkServiceBrowserTest.EncryptedCookies on Windows
entry.content:
This test has not been working on Windows and the root cause

was that the data migration code in content/browser/network_sandbox.cc

was deleting the file called 'cookies' because NTFS used

case-insensitive matching for the 'old' cookie file.



This migration caused the test 'cookies' file created within

the PRE_ fixture to be copied and deleted on the start of the

non-PRE fixture when creating the default network context, since

the migration code believed it to be an old cookies file as

it was contained in the `unsandboxed_data_path` and migration

had occurred.



This always caused there to be no cookies in the 'cookies'

database, since it no longer existing on disk by the time that

the test started executing.



This only had effect on platforms that supplied both an

`unsandboxed_data_path` and also specified

`trigger_migration` to be true, which happened to only

be Windows.



Renaming the file to something other than 'cookies' fixes

this issue, since the migration code is still needed.



The macOS failures are likely a different root cause but

the test can be re-enabled on macOS in a future CL.



BUG=868667

entry.title: snap-groups: Fix crash after transition to tablet
entry.content:
SplitViewOverviewSession is created in clamshell mode, which expects

the window to start resizing and be dragged before we call

`CHECK(presentation_time_recorder_)`. This will:

1. `CHECK(presentation_time_recorder_)` only if we started a resize

2. Bail out if we're not in clamshell mode

since SplitViewOverviewSession will be removed in tablet mode anyway

(b/307631336).

entry.title: [ios] Fix crash when replacing SetUpList MagicStack modules
entry.content:
This change fixes an issue when the SetUpList MagicStack module gets

replaced (with the "All Done" module, for example). The code involves

an array of indexes. When getting the last index and then removing it,

the mistake was that the retrieved index is an index into the

arrangedSubviews array, and not an index into the array of indexes. It

was just easier to use removeLastObject to remove the index from the

array since we alerady know it is the last one.



This crash occurs when the index of the last SetUpList module in the

MagicStack is greater than the number of SetUpList modules. So if there

is one SetUpList module and it is behind the MVTs, it will crash when

the user completes whichever item is left.



Fixed: 1496279

entry.content:
There is an edge case where we are closing customize chrome on a

background navigation that is causing hovercards to be closed.

Previously this was causing a crash issue due to reentrancy where

during the Observe call. However, that has been fixed but we still want

to ensure we close the IPH only when the navigation happens on the

active tab. This is consistent with the behavior for a tab that is

created in the background. That works since the browser instance is

nullptr when the navigation is triggered.
